rical simulations. The outflows include at\nleast a component of relatively compact clouds (10^4-10^5Msun) often observed\nalready at a few tens of pc (in projection) from the core. We also find\nindications that the HI outflow might have a diffuse component, especially in\nlarger sources. Our results support the interpretation that we observe these\nAGNs at different stages in the evolution of the jet-ISM interaction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Oct 2020 19:51:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-17"}
